        "text": "Abstract\n\nAbstract:\n\nGiven a homogeneous ideal in a polynomial ring over $\\Bbb{C}$, we adapt the construction of Newton-Okounkov bodies to obtain a convex subset of Euclidean space such that a suitable integral over this set computes the {\\it Segre zeta function\\/} of the ideal. That is, we extract the numerical information of the Segre class of a subscheme of projective space from an associated (unbounded) Newton-Okounkov convex set. The result generalizes to arbitrary subschemes of projective space the numerical form of a previously known result for monomial schemes."
